        "jobTitle":  "Co-Founder, CEO, Head of AI",
        "summary":  "I’m building Mixio - an AI platform and studio service that empowers production houses to create feature films, animations, and micro-dramas with cinematic consistency, reducing production costs by 60-90% while shrinking timelines from weeks to days.\n​\n\nMy Experience Building in AI\n2017-19: Wrote my IIT-Kharagpur thesis on ML for rural healthcare and shipped my first NLP chatbot leveraging transformers at Airbus.\n\n2019-22: Scaled data-driven growth at BizReach and IgnitusAI, learning how to turn research into revenue-impacting products.\n\n2022-24: Led GenAI initiatives at LegalOn in Tokyo (a global leader in legal AI), deploying GPT-4-powered contract review APIs that serve 2,000+ lawyers daily.\n\n2023-24: Co-founded Viji, an AgriTech marketplace reaching 40k farmers, where I discovered the massive bottleneck of producing high-quality video content at scale.\n\nInsight: That bottleneck became the foundation for Mixio - solving the industry\u0027s inability to get consistent, studio-grade output from standard AI tools.\n​\n\nWhat We Built\nWe have created a hybrid AI filmmaking platform and service tailored for the entertainment industry. Unlike general-purpose video tools that struggle with coherence, Mixio leverages a proprietary engine to ensure scene, character, and object consistency across long-form content (\u003e10 mins).\n​\n\nOur solution allows studios to generate cinematic-grade visuals, control lighting and mood, and produce content in 9 Indian languages. We have already validated this model with 7 active/completed projects and 5 paying studio customers (including partnerships with major players like Balaji Studios and RRE Studios), achieving INR 50L+ in ARR while remaining self-funded.\n​\n\nMy Mission: To make advanced AI practical, accessible and scalable for content creation in organizations.",
